column1:
Oh man... How've I been alive this long
without Hakata tonkotsu!?

I'm awed by the soup's creamy, golden hue,
specked with dots of green onion and dashes
of red ginger...

These three colors combine to form an exquisite
harmony in my bowl! I dare not take another sip,
lest this masterpiece be ruined!
Your, uh... masterpiece is gonna get cold.

Gotta say, these food stalls have their charm.
Even I feel right at home here.

Hey, [1B]S1.
Let me have a little taste.

What's the big deal? Remember, I'm no
ordinary cat.

You're as ordinary as it gets, at least on the 
surface. Don't blame us if you start hackin' up
noodles.

Could you, uh... blow on it? The feline tongue is
sensitive.
So you finally admit you're a cat. Over ramen.

Here, Makoto, have some of my chashu pork.
They say it'll boost your energy!
Thanks. You guys are the best.
How's your lower back doing, Mako-chan?

Better, after a nice, hot bath. That always seems
to do the trick.

That being said, I probably shouldn't be on the
road tomorrow, if only to avoid causing an
accident.

All right, then we'll take the day off. Guess we
should hit up Gramps and let him know we're
staying another night.

Then let's find Makoto a massage place for
tomorrow! I say the girl deserves it.
Got it. I'll locate the best venue there is.

I gotta say though, it is kinda rough having only
one driver. We oughta get our license soon,
[1B]S1.
I believe Haru has one already.

That is true... Though I am pretty lacking in
experience.

But don't you worry, Mako-chan! If for any
reason you're not up to it, I'll take the wheel!
Huh!? Oh, well... As much as I appreciate that...

Is something wrong, Makoto? You don't look so
well.

Aw crap. We better dig in before the noodles
get soggy!
Damn, I'm stuffed! Now I can die happy...

I suppose I should also throw in the towel. Not a
drop of soup remains.

I can't believe you guys got seven noodle
refills. You'd think this was a ramen buffet...
Well, I see you boys had quite a meal!

I should mention, customers who order 
over five sets of noodles get a free souvenir
bowl!
For real!? Thanks for the hookup, Pops!
Ah... This should serve as good decor. Surely it will brighten up our vehicle's interior.

A ramen shop where? I'm gonna guess it's
Fukuoka, assuming that you're going at a
decent pace.

All right. Sounds like you're going at a decent
pace, then.

Anyway, I'm calling to let you know I think I
found our guy.

I'll give you more details in person. Saves us time
and energy.

Sorry it's so sudden, but how soon do you think
you can be at Kyoto?

I explained why it might take a little
longer than expected...

Niijima's down for the count, huh?
Damn, of all the rotten luck...

Then what about a bullet train? Or, wait, can't
you ask Okumura? Doesn't she have a license?

All she'd have to do is take the Sanyodo from
Fukuoka to Kyoto. Not a tough drive by any
means.

I hate to lay the pressure on, but we don't have
much time. A lot rides on this.

Zenkichi hung up abruptly. I should
tell everyone what he wants...
Wait, so he knows who the mastermind is!?
Finally, we get to bust this effin' punk.

Then let's leave tomorrow morning. Being tired
is no excuse to delay our mission.

As true as that is, be careful not to hurt yourself,
Makoto.
